gomodel:SYNGO_4669  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1E-F: Authors utilized a pHluorin reporter (super-ecliptic pHluorin: SEP) fused to the luminal C-terminal portions of Stx7 to image localization of Stx7 in cultured hippocampal neurons. Stx7-SEP exhibited unique behavior, i.e., stimulation at 10 Hz failed to elicit a clear fluorescence increase, while 40 Hz stimulation caused a robust increase up to ~40%.\n\nFigure 2: Exocytosis of Stx7-SEP vesicles requires HFS. Authors continuously monitored changes in SEP fluorescence at individual boutons with various stimulation frequencies ranging from 5 to 40 Hz at 5 min intervals. Unlike SypHy, which reliably exhibited a robust exocytotic fluorescence increase irrespective of stimulation frequency, Stx7-SEP hardly responded during 5 Hz or 10 Hz stimulation, while it showed robust fluorescence increases at 20 and 40 Hz in the same boutons.\n\nAuthors conclude; \"Our results collectively indicate that endosomal fusion supported by Stx7, presumably together with its cognate SNAREs, is responsible for generating a functionally distinct recycling pool of SVs\". Experimental description: - Primary hippocampal cultures were prepared from embryonic day 16 ICR mice\n- pHluorin reporter (super-ecliptic pHluorin: SEP) fused to the luminal C-terminal portions of Stx7\n- rabbit polyclonal anti-Stx7 antibody (BethylLaboratories; A304-512A),\n\n'\"To generate recombinant proteins as standards for quantification analysis, Stx7-NTD (a.a. 1-149) and Syb2-ΔTMD (a.a. 1-94) (accession no. NM_009497.3) were amplified by PCR, and cloned into the BamHI site and SalI site of pGEX6P-1. Lentiviral vectors carrying mCherry and either scrambled shRNA (CCTAAGGTTAAGTCGCCCTCG), mouse Stx7 shRNA-#1 (CGATATGATTGACAGCATAGA), or mouse Stx7 shRNA-#2; (GAAGCTGATATTATGGACATT) were obtained from VectorBuilder Biotechnology Co. Ltd.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4669" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

